You are working on the IEBA frontend project.

Tech stack:
- React
- TypeScript
- Vite
- TanStack Query for data fetching
- shadcn/ui for UI components
- Tailwind CSS

Project architecture rules:

1. Follow feature-based folder structure.

src/
  features/
    <feature-name>/
      components/
      hooks/
      queries/
      mutations/
      pages/
      keys.ts
      index.ts

2. Use TanStack Query for API calls.
Do not use fetch directly inside components.

3. UI components must use shadcn/ui components.

4. Reusable UI components should go inside:
src/components/ui

5. Hooks should be placed inside:
features/<feature>/hooks

6. Queries must go inside:
features/<feature>/queries

7. Mutations must go inside:
features/<feature>/mutations

8. Use TypeScript types everywhere.

9. Avoid creating unnecessary files.

10. Follow clean and readable code practices.

11. Never use any type in typescript, follow strict types.

12. Follow SRP.

13. Always use lazy loading.